# Supabase Production Environment Variables
# Copy this file and fill in your production Supabase credentials
# from https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/YOUR_PROJECT/settings/api

# Supabase Production URL
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co

# Supabase Anonymous Key (safe for client-side use)
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-production-anon-key-here

# HOW TO GET THESE VALUES:
# =========================
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project (or create a new one)
# 3. Go to Settings → API
# 4. Copy:
#    - Project URL → SUPABASE_URL
#    - anon/public key → SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# IMPORTANT:
# ==========
# - Use the "anon" key, NOT the "service_role" key
# - The anon key is safe for client-side use (protected by RLS)
# - Never commit this file to Git
# - For Vercel: Add these as environment variables in project settings
